sentences: Elvin Estela (born March 14, 1977), better known by his stage name Nobody, is an American hip hop producer based in Los Angeles, California.
Better Propaganda placed him at number 73 on the "Top 100 Artists of the Decade" list.
Nobody's solo debut album, Soulmates, was released on Ubiquity Records in 2000.
He released the third solo album, And Everything Else..., on Plug Research in 2005.
Nobody wrote the article about 1960s psychedelic rock for XLR8R in 2006.
In 2008, Estela released the album, Western Water Music Vol.
It is the official follow-up to his 2003 album, Pacific Draft: Western Water Music Vol.
The fourth solo album, One for All Without Hesitation, was released on Alpha Pup Records in 2010.
He returned with Vivid Green, an album featuring Cedric Bixler-Zavala, Nocando and Baths, in 2013.
